<h2 id="68b2e7b22df2e"><strong>Kim Byung Hoon&rsquo;s business breakthroughs and recognition</strong></h2>

<p>Kim Byung Hoon was born on November 5, 1988. He is the founder and chief executive of APR Corp, which is a South Korean beauty-tech company. This company is known for its tech-infused skincare devices such as Medicube and the Booster Pro. In 2014, Kim founded this company after graduating from university. His early ventures included developing a virtual fitting service and a dating app during his time at Yonsei University.</p>

<p>He started experimenting with cosmetics but then transitioned into at-home beauty devices, which marked a major step for APR. His vision has always been about building something like Apple or Tesla in the beauty industry&mdash;placing technology at the heart of innovation in skincare.</p>

<p>Kim Byung Hoon&rsquo;s company, APR, went public in February 2024, and his 31% stake in the company is estimated at US$1.3 billion. The company&rsquo;s market value stands at a capitalisation of over US$4 billion, and shares have risen roughly 200% this year.</p>

<p>APR gained global popularity through TikTok and other digital platforms, especially with its Medicube brand and Booster Pro device going viral thanks to influencer endorsements, including Kylie Jenner and Hailey Bieber. Despite being a billionaire, Kim is actively involved in day-to-day operations, consumer feedback and weekend strategy sessions.</p>
